result.execSummary:
The defendant Kevin E Callaway was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Kevin E Callaway is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Kevin E Callaway was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Kevin E Callaway in court, in custody with attorney Ryan T. Frank.  Christine M. Genda appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Cases called: 15CM137, 15CM297, 15CM173, & 15CM138.  Recommendations given by ADA Genda.  Rights/Elements.  Defendant pled no contest to Ct. 1 of 15CM173 with repeater dismissed, and to Cts. 1 and 3 of 15CM297.   Court found guilty.  Judgment was entered.  15CM138 dismissed.  15CM137 all counts dismissed but read in.  In 15CM297 Cts. 1 & 3.  On Ct. 1 court imposed but stayed a 2 year prison sentence.  Ct. 3  1 year prison sentence, consecutive to Ct. 1, stayed. Placed defendant on probation for 2 years each count.  Cts. 2,4, & 5 are dismissed.  In 15CM173 Ct. 1  court withheld sentencing placed defendant on probation for 2 years.  Court dismissed repeater enhancer, and dismissed Cts. 2,3, & 4.  Conditions of probation on both cases include:  AODA and comply.  Psychological evaluation and comply.  No contact of any kind including no third party contact with C.H. or her children A.H. or K.H.  $443.00 costs each count.  Must reside with his mother for 90 days at her residence.  In 90 days there is to be a review in court to check on housing and employment for defendant.  No conditional jail time,  due to his current time spent in custody.  Must report to probation by noon on 7/22/15.  6 month review.
